items.title: Accenture Q1 Results: Co posts $17.7 billion in revenue, beats estimates
items.description: Accenture surpassed first-quarter revenue expectations, driven by increased demand for AI integration services.  New bookings reached $18.7 billion, exceeding the previous year's figure. Revenue hit $17.7 billion, outperforming analyst projections.  The company raised its annual revenue growth forecast to 4%-7%.
